    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-LSzQXqdZh38/UE0M4KWpuII/AAAAAAAAAos/wrBm3DDdlpw/s1600/1347226831_application-x-ruby.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-LSzQXqdZh38/UE0M4KWpuII/AAAAAAAAAos/wrBm3DDdlpw/s1600/1347226831_application-x-ruby.png" /></a></div>


<p><br />Ruby language doesn&rsquo;t have an official <i>Style Guide</i>. That&rsquo;s why I&rsquo;ve decided to collect <b>most </b>interesting style guides in one place.<br /><br /><h3>My Favorites:</h3><ul><li><a href="http://davetron5000.github.com/ruby-style/">davetron5000&rsquo;s Ruby Style Guide</a></li><li><a href="http://chneukirchen.github.com/rps/">Ruby Packaging Standard</a></li><li><a href="https://github.com/bbatsov/ruby-style-guide">The Ruby Style Guide, by Bozhidar Batsov</a>&nbsp; (<a href="https://github.com/styleguide/ruby">GitHub Ruby Styleguide</a> is based on this)</li><li><a href="http://en.opensuse.org/openSUSE:Ruby_coding_conventions">openSUSE Ruby coding conventions</a></li></ul>Others:<br /><ul><li><a href="http://www.caliban.org/ruby/rubyguide.shtml#style">Ruby Style Guidelines by Ian Macdonald</a></li><li><a href="http://whynotwiki.com/Ruby_/_Coding_conventions">Ruby / Coding conventions</a></li><li><a href="http://rails.nuvvo.com/lesson/5017-ruby-coding-convention">Ruby Coding Convention by Libin Pan</a></li><li>Noel&rsquo;s Rappin <a href="http://pathfindersoftware.com/2008/10/elements-of-ruby-style/" target="_blank">Elements of ruby style </a> and <a href="http://pathfindersoftware.com/2008/10/ruby-stylista/">Ruby Stylista</a></li><li><a href="http://code.google.com/p/tokland/wiki/RubyIdioms">Ruby Idioms by Arnau Sanchez</a></li></ul></p>
